[SN]TITLE[SN]
Stabbing victim closes Swansea police station

[SN]FIRST-SENTENCE[SN]
Swansea central police station has been closed after a stabbing victim sought shelter from his attackers inside.

[SN]RESTBODY[SN]
The man, who had stab wounds on his arms and face, fled into the reception area. Picton Terrace in Mount Pleasant has also been sealed off.
Two men, aged 39 and 28, have been arrested.
The man went into the police station just after 15:00 BST on Monday and has been taken to hospital - his injuries are not thought be life-threatening.
A South Wales Police spokesman said: "Police in Swansea are currently dealing with an ongoing incident in the city centre.
"Police officers are in attendance at several locations in connection with the incident and an investigation is continuing."
